sql:
SELECT MAX(price) AS most_expensive_product
FROM products
WHERE product_id IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT product_id
    FROM order_items
);

external_knowledge:
- "top-rated items" refers to products with an average rating of 4.0 or higher;
- "popular among the customers" implies the items are frequently ordered, with more than 10 orders;
- "high reviews" means the product has a high average rating, at least 4.0 out of 5;
- "frequently ordered" indicates that the products have been ordered more than 10 times.

- "Decent variety of goods" implies a minimum of 2 products available; 
- "Middle range" for average price is considered to be between 10 and 20 units;
- The "hight and lowest price range" refers to the maximum and minimum values of the product prices for each vendor.

- "more than a dozen times" refers to order quantities greater than 10;
- The term "combined amount of products" refers to the sum of the product quantities available in stock for each vendor;
- The question focuses on vendors who have sold products in larger quantities, indicating a higher demand.
